## 🧪 **MANDATORY: Test-Driven Generation (TDG) Standard Operating Procedure** ✅ **ZERO TOLERANCE**

**🚨 CRITICAL: ALL AI-generated code (Claude, Gemini, or any AI agent) MUST follow Test-Driven Generation methodology**

### **🎯 TDG Core Principles (MANDATORY COMPLIANCE)**

**✅ REQUIRED TDG WORKFLOW:**
1.0 - **TEST FIRST**: Write comprehensive tests BEFORE any code generation
2.0 - **AI GENERATION**: Generate code to satisfy existing tests (never generate untested code)
3.0 - **VALIDATION**: Ensure all tests pass with generated code
4.0 - **REFACTOR**: Improve code quality while maintaining test coverage
5.0 - **DOCUMENTATION**: Update docs to reflect TDG methodology compliance

**❌ ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN:**
1.0 - **Code-First Generation**: VIOLATION - Never generate code before tests exist
2.0 - **Untested Code**: VIOLATION - All generated code must have corresponding tests
3.0 - **Post-Hoc Testing**: VIOLATION - Tests must be written BEFORE code generation
4.0 - **Skipping TDG**: VIOLATION - No exceptions allowed for any AI-generated code
5.0 - **Manual Testing Only**: VIOLATION - Automated tests required for all generated code

### **🔬 TDG Implementation Rules (ZERO TOLERANCE)**

**✅ MANDATORY TDG SEQUENCE:**

**1.0 - Test Design Phase (FIRST ACTIVITY)**
```bash
# ✅ REQUIRED: Start with test design before any code generation
1.1 - Analyze requirements and identify test scenarios
1.2 - Write failing tests that specify desired behavior
1.3 - Validate test structure and coverage completeness
1.4 - Commit tests to version control before proceeding
```

**2.0 - AI Code Generation Phase (CONTROLLED)**
```bash
# ✅ REQUIRED: Generate code to satisfy pre-existing tests
2.1 - Run existing tests to confirm they fail appropriately
2.2 - Generate minimal code to make tests pass
2.3 - Validate that all tests now pass with generated code
2.4 - Ensure no breaking changes to existing test suite
```

**3.0 - Validation and Quality Phase (SYSTEMATIC)**
```bash
# ✅ REQUIRED: Comprehensive validation before acceptance
3.1 - Run complete test suite to ensure no regressions
3.2 - Validate code quality meets enterprise standards
3.3 - Confirm TDG methodology compliance documentation
3.4 - Update project documentation with TDG evidence
```

### **🤖 AI Agent TDG Compliance (MANDATORY)**

**✅ CLAUDE AGENT REQUIREMENTS:**
1.0 - **Test Analysis**: Always analyze existing tests before code generation
2.0 - **Test-First Prompt**: Include test requirements in all code generation requests
3.0 - **Test Validation**: Verify generated code passes all tests before presenting
4.0 - **TDG Documentation**: Document TDG compliance in all code generation sessions
5.0 - **Quality Gates**: Apply TDG validation as mandatory quality gate

**✅ GEMINI AGENT REQUIREMENTS:**
1.0 - **Test Context**: Include test scenarios in all Gemini API requests
2.0 - **Test-Driven Prompts**: Structure prompts to emphasize test-first approach
3.0 - **Validation Integration**: Validate Gemini responses against existing tests
4.0 - **Claude Supervision**: Claude Supervisor validates Gemini TDG compliance
5.0 - **Fallback Testing**: Ensure fallback modes maintain TDG methodology

