2.0 - **Wait for Completion**: MUST wait patiently for ALL compilation and test execution to complete naturally
3.0 - **No Interruption**: NEVER interrupt or cancel test execution due to time constraints
4.0 - **Extended Timeouts**: Use maximum available timeout values (7200000ms / 2 hours minimum)
5.0 - **Compilation Fixes First**: Fix ALL compilation errors before attempting test execution
6.0 - **Dependencies Installed**: Ensure ALL testing dependencies (PropCheck, ExUnitProperties) are properly installed
7.0 - **Full Test Suite**: Execute complete TDD test suite without limiting test cases prematurely

**❌ ABSOLUTELY FORBIDDEN:**
1.0 - **Timeout Interruption**: VIOLATION - Never interrupt tests due to timeout
2.0 - **Impatient Execution**: VIOLATION - Never rush or cancel long-running tests
3.0 - **Incomplete Testing**: VIOLATION - Never skip test execution due to compilation issues
4.0 - **Dependency Shortcuts**: VIOLATION - Never run tests without proper dependency installation
5.0 - **Limited Test Execution**: VIOLATION - Never artificially limit test cases without technical reason
